# JWT Authentication Boilerplate

This is a simple boilerplate to start any new JWT based auth project in Typescript, ExpressJS.

## Prerequisites

- Node, with version 16.x.x
- Typescript and Nodemon

## Setup & Installation

1. Install dependencies using npm

`npm i`

2. Create .env file at the root directory and populate it with the contents of `.env.sample` file.

## Usage

For simplicity, all the routes, controllers and services are placed in the same file. Feel free to take them out and create your own directory structure in your main project.

1. Run `npm run start:auth` on a terminal to start the auth server which contains all authentication related APIs.
2. Run `npm run start:service` on another terminal to test the authorization functionality.

Article referred for this project - https://medium.com/@prashantramnyc/authenticate-rest-apis-in-node-js-using-jwt-json-web-tokens-f0e97669aad3
